<p>"The trailer offers a first look at Pax Armata, a Private Military Corporation bankrolled by former NATO states whose agenda threatens to throw the world into global conflict," reads a line from the game's description. "This sets the scene for what players can expect on the battlefield--both in multiplayer and the return of the series' single player campaign. In Battlefield 6, the series' incredible blend of visceral combat, epic warfare, and player freedom returns. Blow through walls and bring down buildings for a tactical advantage or take to the skies in white-knuckle dogfights. Take part in a war filled with tanks, fighter jets, and sweeping combat at a grand scale but remember: the deadliest weapon is your squad."</p><p>This trailer was focused on Battlefield 6's campaign, but the multiplayer reveal is set for July 31. This trailer also did not reveal a release date or any information about the open beta.</p><p>The Battlefield 6 multiplayer reveal event takes place on Thursday, July 31, beginning at 11:30 AM PT / 2:30 PM ET. It will take live, featuring developers from Battlefield Studios discussing the project.</p><p>"This epic showcase will lift the curtain on Battlefield 6's much-anticipated multiplayer features and demonstrate why this is the most ambitious title in the series' history, with an explosive showcase of some of the jaw-dropping maps players will battle across, the suite of modes both new and returning, and much much more," EA said.</p><p>Battlefield 6 is rumored to launch on October 10, and it's expected t come to PS5, Xbox Series X|S, and PC. It's the first new entry in the series since 2021's Battlefield 2042.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
